cs.SY, cs.AI, cs.CR, cs.LG, cs.RO 

This paper deals with the development of a framework for using adversarial deep reinforcement learning to design observer strategies that are robust to adversarial errors in information channels. The paper focuses on autonomous control systems, which are typically studied in the subfield of robotics (cs.RO). The use of deep reinforcement learning and neural networks as function approximators suggests that the paper may also belong to the subfields of artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The paper also deals with cyber-attacks and sensor failures, which are typically studied in the subfield of computer security (cs.CR). Finally, the use of reinforcement learning and control theory suggests that the paper may also belong to the subfield of systems and control (cs.SY).
